-- China May Allow Yuan Funds in Hong Kong by End of Year, 21st Century Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-01T00:23:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/china-may-allow-yuan-funds-in-hong-kong-by-end-of-year-21st-century-says.html

          
          
             China may allow mainland brokerages
and funds to set up yuan-denominated funds in Hong Kong for
investing in the Chinese stock market by as soon as the end of
this year, the 21st Century Business Herald reported late
yesterday on its website, citing an unidentified Chinese bank
official based in Hong Kong.  
